			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Kompani Group, a fast-growing, South Florida, based strategy firm with capacities in strategy, branding, design, interactive, technology and marketing solutions. We have an exciting opportunity for an organized, independent, Senior User Experience Designer</p>
<p>
	<strong>Job Summary</strong></p>
<p>
	The Senior User Experience Designer role is unique, and for the right candidate it will prove an amazing opportunity. Employing the UX methodologies, the position will own the entire end-to-end process of bringing new functionality to our client&rsquo;s sites: from scoping the project with with the CTO, CEO and at times client stake holders, to wire-framing/prototyping a proof of concept to creating the interactive elements to guidng the new functionality live into production.</p>
<p>
	Our goal is to create the most elegantly usable websites so we&#39;re looking for someone who wants to both be part of a dynamic, creative team and have ambitions to be a rock-star UX designer.</p>
<p>
	The Senior User Experience Designer should demonstrate a rich but versatile aesthetic, be a little geeky when it comes to usability, and intuitively understand and solve for the nuances of web design patterns. In addition, and quite significantly, the role needs to interface with our strategy and programming teams to help us realize their business goals.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Meet with internal stakeholders to define functional solutions for business problems</li>
	<li>
		Create wireframes or prototypes as proof of concept</li>
	<li>
		Design interaction, look and feel</li>
	<li>
		Write non-technical specification for programmers</li>
	<li>
		Final-pass QA</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		BA/BS or MA/MS in Graphic Design, Human-Computer Interaction, Interaction Design, Human Factors or related field.</li>
	<li>
		3+ years of experience in designing and prototyping for the web; ecommerce experience is preferred, but not required.</li>
	<li>
		Knowledge of user-centered design principles coupled with a &quot;don&#39;t make me think&quot; understanding of usability.</li>
	<li>
		Strong Photoshop and Illustrator skills; high-fidelity prototyping experience is a plus.</li>
	<li>
		Ability to write non-technical specs for programmers</li>
	<li>
		Demonstrated ability to manage expectations, meet firm deadlines and thrive in a dynamic work environment.</li>
	<li>
		Knowledge of coding/scripting is not necessary, but a good understanding of what HTML, CSS, and JavaScript are capable of bringing to the modern web is desired.</li>
	<li>
		Above all else: good intuition.</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
